{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Unverified ACO tokens let attackers sweep arbitrary writer-held ERC20 balances","locations":["onchain_auto/0xe7597f774fd0a15a617894dc39d45a28b97afa4f/Contract.sol:1","onchain_auto/src/FlawVerifier.sol:230","onchain_auto/src/FlawVerifier.sol:271"],"claim":"`write()` trusts the caller-supplied `acoToken` for `collateral()`, `strikeAsset()`, and mint behavior. A malicious token can make `transferFrom`/`mintTo` succeed without moving real collateral, then `_sellACOTokens()` uses the untrusted `strikeAsset()` value and transfers the writer's entire balance of that token to the caller.","impact":"Any ERC20 balance already resident in the writer, including WETH or stablecoins, can be permissionlessly drained without supplying real collateral or selling real option tokens.","paths":["Deploy a fake token that implements the expected interface, returns a malicious collateral token that always reports successful `transferFrom`, and reports the target asset from `strikeAsset()`","Call `write(fakeToken, 1, attackerEOA, \"\")` while sending the minimum ETH required by `write()`","`_sellACOTokens()` succeeds, then transfers the writer's full balance of the chosen strike asset to the attacker"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Caller-chosen exchange can steal the writer's entire ETH balance","locations":["onchain_auto/0xe7597f774fd0a15a617894dc39d45a28b97afa4f/Contract.sol:1"],"claim":"The caller fully controls `exchangeAddress` via `setExchange(exchangeAddress)`, and `_sellACOTokens()` blindly forwards `address(this).balance` to `_exchange.call(...)` before any accounting. There is no validation that the target is a trusted exchange or that the ETH returned corresponds to the current trade.","impact":"Any ETH sitting in the writer, including prior premiums or accidentally stranded funds, can be sent to an attacker-controlled EOA or contract and never returned.","paths":["Wait until the writer holds ETH","Call `write(...)` with `exchangeAddress` set to an attacker-controlled EOA or contract and benign calldata","The low-level call transfers the writer's full ETH balance to the attacker-controlled destination, and the rest of the function cannot recover it"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"ETH-collateral writes can be underfunded with protocol-owned ETH","locations":["onchain_auto/0xe7597f774fd0a15a617894dc39d45a28b97afa4f/Contract.sol:1"],"claim":"For ETH-collateral series, `write()` only checks `msg.value > 0` and then calls `mintToPayable{value: collateralAmount}(msg.sender)`. If `collateralAmount` exceeds `msg.value`, the shortfall is silently funded from the writer's pre-existing ETH balance.","impact":"Attackers can mint options collateralized by the writer's native ETH instead of their own, externalizing collateral losses to the protocol or prior users.","paths":["Wait until the writer holds ETH","Call `write(validEthCollateralToken, largeCollateralAmount, exchangeAddress, exchangeData)` while sending only 1 wei","`mintToPayable{value: collateralAmount}` consumes the writer's ETH balance to collateralize options minted to the attacker"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Premium settlement pays out whole-contract balances instead of the current trade delta","locations":["onchain_auto/0xe7597f774fd0a15a617894dc39d45a28b97afa4f/Contract.sol:1"],"claim":"After the exchange call, `_sellACOTokens()` transfers `_balanceOfERC20(token, address(this))` for ERC20 strikes or `address(this).balance` for ETH, rather than the incremental proceeds generated by the current write.","impact":"Residual strike assets or ETH from earlier users, failed fills, partial settlements, or unsolicited transfers can be permissionlessly claimed by the next caller whose trade reaches the same payout branch.","paths":["A previous interaction or direct transfer leaves strike tokens or ETH inside the writer","A later caller invokes `write()` for a series whose strike asset matches that balance, or uses an ETH-settling path","The contract forwards the entire leftover balance to the later caller as if it were their premium"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Any WETH balance can permanently brick ETH-strike writes","locations":["onchain_auto/0xe7597f774fd0a15a617894dc39d45a28b97afa4f/Contract.sol:1","onchain_auto/src/FlawVerifier.sol:240","onchain_auto/src/FlawVerifier.sol:255"],"claim":"For ETH-strike options, `_sellACOTokens()` calls `IWETH(weth).withdraw(wethBalance)` when the writer holds any WETH. The resulting ETH is sent from the WETH contract, but `receive()` reverts unless `msg.sender == _exchange`, so the withdraw path always reverts when WETH is present.","impact":"A 1 wei WETH transfer is enough to poison the contract and make ETH-strike writes revert until the WETH balance is somehow removed, but the contract exposes no recovery path to do so.","paths":["Transfer any amount of WETH directly to the writer","Call `write()` for an ETH-strike ACO token","`_sellACOTokens()` attempts `WETH.withdraw`, the callback hits `receive()`, and the transaction reverts because the sender is WETH rather than `_exchange`"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Missing access control on write() function","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`write()` being public is not inherently a vulnerability for this pattern. The reportable harm comes from untrusted token/exchange inputs and whole-balance accounting, which are captured in other findings."},{"title":"Unchecked return value on WETH.withdraw","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`IWETH.withdraw(uint256)` does not return a value in the referenced interface or canonical WETH9 implementation, so there is no ignored boolean result to check."}]}
